definition: sandwich cookie/(jocularly) sb who is caught between two opposing parties/sb who is between the hammer and the anvil
Taiwan pr. used in 夾生|夹生[jia1 sheng1] and 夾竹桃|夹竹桃[jia1 zhu2 tao2]
to press from either side/to place in between/to sandwich/to carry sth under armpit/wedged between/between/to intersperse/to mix/to mingle/clip/folder/Taiwan pr. [jia2]
one of the Eight Trigrams 八卦[ba1 gua4], symbolizing heaven/male principle/☰/ancient Chinese compass point: 315° (northwest)

sentences.english: This cookie bar is one of the examples.
sentences.chinese: 這個夾心餅乾就是其中的一個例子。

sentences.english: In autumn and winter, the air was crispy and sweet, like biscuits.
sentences.chinese: 秋天和冬天，空氣脆而甜潤，像夾心餅乾。
